So today is February 20th, 2021 and it's a super special and very important day as 42 years ago my amazing, handsome, hard working, and loving husband Albert was born. We recently 3 weeks ago moved to Cape Coral, Florida from the Naples/Ft Myers area.  It has been our dream to find a place in the Cape and our dream had finally become a reality. I was born and raised in St Louis, Missouri home of provel cheese and Imo's thin crust pizza.  Imo'a Pizza is hands down St Louis's best place for pizza PERIOD! My hubby hails from Jersey and is a fan of Chicago style deep dish pizza which honestly I had never tried until today.  My husband is a simple easy going guy and he wanted to tey Chicago Pizza in the Cape and rent a RedBox movie for his birthday and we did just that.  So for lunch I called the restaurant and ordered a 12" deep dish ham and bacon puzza, a small side salad, and a chicken Parmesan sandwhich with tots. Now as I mentioned earlier I love thin and crispy crust and have always been afraid to order and try deep dish but his birthday his choice.  Everything was absolutely perfect from the order taker on the phone, to the fast delivery, and the pizza was beyond compare to anything I have ever eaten that was called pizza.  The ham was like a freah sliced deli ham and the bacon was homecooked and crispy crunchy just how I like it.  i was amazed that there was absolutely no grease on my hands from holding it and the everything was just ABSOLUTELY PERFECT HANDS DOWN!! We have definitely found our go to place for pizza and will never order anywhere else AGAIN!  For those of you who left less than a 5 star perfect review maybe you were reviewing the wrong restaurant lol because there is nothing I can say that would be negative or anything I could find to suggest a better product or better service! THANK YOU CHICAGO PIZZA FOR MAKING MY HUSBAND'S 42nd BIRTHDAY ONE OF THE BEST YET!  WE WILL DEF SEE YOU AT LEAST ONCE A WEEK!!❤❤❤💯💯💯❤❤❤💯💯💯❤❤❤💯💯💯👍👍👍

So, as this is our favorite pizza, by far in Cape Coral, I was disturbed at the flagrant disregard for COVID precautions. My sister nearly died from COVID. Please use your brains and follow CDC guidelines. Until you change things, we will take our business to Lelulos's, our second favorite--they are doing everything right. This is not a political issue--you are contributing to peoples' deaths, quite likely! We are snowbirds, and have been religiously coming here for the past six years, at least twice a month. Forget it. Not worth the risk. This is absolutely pathetic--think of your patrons and your employees! After posting review, the legitimacy was questioned. I have spent a lot of money and been very loyal the last few years. When I walk in and masks are not being worn, forget it! I have had cordial conversations with the owner (from MA, by the way on several occasions) and always tip on take out. Don't question me! Your employees need to mask up! Get a clue! This is absolutely a legitimate review. You have great pizza, better than Lelulos, but you are adding fire to the pandemic by not following CDC guidelines. All your employees need to wear masks, period. Get it together.
